hours of sleep and still groggy during the day during the summer vacation i've gotten into a routine of going to bed at a m and waking up at p m i sleep solidly through not getting up at all and yet i'm groggy when i get up i yawn for the rest of the day and evening and i feel very tired if i'm woken up before even if i've gotten hours of sleep during school days i'm forced to have a more conventional schedule getting around hours of sleep a night i have a hard time getting up in the morning and yawn all day is this normal should i get checked out sounds like your body is having a hard time adjusting to the bouncing back and forth of sleep schedules i work nite shift and on my days off of work i have a more routine schedule going to bed at p and getting up at a to take my kids to school on the days i work i go to bed around a and get up at p i don't feel rested if i wake before i've been doing this schedule for years now so my body is adjusted but for you who is not used to it you will struggle our body's naturally fight a night shift awake time b c it's not normal i would try sticking to a somewhat normal routine even in the summer time try to get to bed no later than pm and wake around the time you normally do this should help you not feel so tired for the first few months you might feel groggy even with hours of sleep b c you body needs time to adjust once adjusted you should feel much better the hours of sleep you were getting was too much for your body which is why you felt tired all day hope this helps Daylight saving time Insomnia Delayed sleep phase syndrome Out-of-body experience Apollo 8 Mattress Jet lag Fertility awareness Bon Jovi Skinny Dip Polyphasic sleep Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 March Narcolepsy Episodes of Lost (Season 1) USS Alden (DD-211) Lucid dreaming Labour economics Dream Siesta The Shining (film) STS-59 The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Weight training The Adventures of Pete & Pete Sleep apnea Futurama (